Justin Rose admitted he lost to the better man as Jordan Spieth won his first Masters title in emphatic fashion. 

The 21-year-old finished 18 under to beat Rose and Phil Mickelson by four shots and become the second youngest Masters winner - after Tiger Woods in 1997. 

Spieth became only the fourth player after Jack Nicklaus, Ray Floyd and Tiger Woods to reach 17 under. Only Spieth and Wood ever got to 18 under, and Spieth is now the only person to reach 19 under. 

