Rose, who finished joint-second with Phil Mickelson on 14 under, said: 'Phenomenal, what a month of golf Jordan's had. Awesome composure; every time I thought there was a chink in the armour he would come out and hole an eight foot putt.

'Jordan seems to have that same quality right now and he's very comfortable playing with a lead. 14 under round here I'll take that every year and take my chances.' 

World No 1 Rory McIlroy, who needed to win to complete a career grand slam, finished fourth after a closing 66 and added: 'Jordan started fantastically well and has kept his foot down and been really impressive.' 

Tributes poured in for Spieth from his fellow players and other stars as the world reacted to the young Texan's impressive display.  

